\f0\b\fs26 \cf0 \cb2 Laird Hamilton
\b0  (born March 2, 1964) is an {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 American}} {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Big_wave_surfing"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 big-wave surfer}}, co-inventor of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tow-in_surfing"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 tow-in surfing}}, and an occasional fashion and action-sports model. He is married to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gabrielle_Reece"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Gabrielle Reece}}, a professional volleyball player, television personality, and model. Hamilton and his family split their time between residences in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kauai"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Kauai}},{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hawaii"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Hawaii}}, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malibu,_California"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Malibu, California}}.\
