\fs26 \nosupersub \
In 1995 Hamilton met women's professional {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Volleyball"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 volleyball}} player and New York fashion model {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gabrielle_Reece"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Gabrielle Reece}} in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Los_Angeles,_California"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Los Angeles, California}} after a television interview. They later married on November 30, 1997. In 1996, People magazine named Hamilton one of the 50 Most Beautiful People in the World, and in the same year Hamilton pushed for and took from his future wife the correspondent position for the syndicated cable series 'The Extremists'.{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laird_Hamilton#cite_note-mahalo.com-5"}}{\fldrslt 
\fs22 \cf3 [5]}} In 1989 Reece had been named by {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elle_(magazine)"}}{\fldrslt 
\i \cf3 Elle}} magazine as one of the Five Most Beautiful Women in the World.
