\fs26 \nosupersub \
By the late 1990s, Hamilton continued with {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windsurfing"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 windsurfing}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Waterskiing"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 waterskiing}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kitesurfing"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 kitesurfing}}. In 1996 Hamilton and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manu_Bertin"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Manu Bertin}} were instrumental in demonstrating and popularizing kitesurfing off the Hawaiian coast of Maui. In 1999 Hamilton sailed his windsurfer between the Hawaiian islands of Oahu and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kauai"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Kaua\uc0\u699 i}}, some fifty miles away, in just under six hours..
