\fs26 \cf0 \cb2 In February 2008 Hamilton joined the board of directors of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/H2O_Audio"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 H2O Audio}}, a watersports music company in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Diego_California"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 San Diego California}}. He had used H2O Audio products on many of his long distance paddling endeavors before joining the company.{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laird_Hamilton#cite_note-14"}}{\fldrslt 
\fs22 \cf3 [14]}} Later in 2008 he published a book which he describes as not an autobiography, but discussing his philosophy of life.{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laird_Hamilton#cite_note-15"}}{\fldrslt 
\fs22 \cf3 [15]}}\
Despite being one of the best known surfers since the time of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Duke_Kahanamoku"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Duke Kahanamoku}}, the matured Hamilton avoids self-promotion. He serves as an ambassador of surfing and watersports and occasional lifeguard to other tow-in surfers.\
Hamilton is also an environmental activist. He joined a protest in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malibu,_California"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Malibu}} against a proposed plant that was to be built in the area, which would affect the quality of the water. Other celebrities attended the event including {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pierce_Brosnan"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Pierce Brosnan}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Halle_Berry"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Halle Berry}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ted_Danson"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Ted Danson}}.\
